<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-11-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-11-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="346" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-11-27"><hi rend="italic">November 27,
                            1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Minister for foreign affairs states war vessel not ordered Bluefields, and
                        British notification to Nicaraguan commissioner merely caveat pending
                        discussion, and not intended as conclusive. Dispatches now on way explain
                        situation.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bayard.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>